# Mobile React Native + Expo Rules
- Use React Native + Expo as the official mobile stack for apps/mobile.
- Keep the mobile app connected to the same backend API and shared contracts used by web, admin, and courier clients.
- Prefer a feature-oriented architecture with clear presentation, domain/use-case, API-client, and shared UI boundaries.
- Use TypeScript strictly; avoid untyped navigation params, API responses, and persisted state.
- Use Expo-compatible libraries by default and document any native-module exception before introducing it.
- Centralize API clients, auth/session handling, serialization, retries, and standard API error mapping.
- Keep token handling secure; never persist raw secrets in source control and avoid exposing sensitive auth data unnecessarily.
- Design mobile-first with responsive layouts, accessible touch targets, safe-area handling, and clear loading/empty/error states.
- Keep push notification handling, deep links, and device-token lifecycle in a dedicated integration layer.
- Do not mirror web-only assumptions into mobile flows without checking mobile UX needs.
- Do not implement mobile features before the approved mobile phase/batch.
